ing: 1 tablespoon olive oil, or as needed
1 jalapeno pepper - stemmed, seeded, and diced
1 pinch chili powder, or to taste
des: "A little leftover rotisserie chicken makes a zesty stew."
ins: Heat olive oil in a 2-quart pot over medium heat; cook and stir green onions, celery, jalapeno pepper, garlic, and chili powder in the hot oil until celery is tender, 5 to 10 minutes. Add chicken broth, coconut water, and cilantro and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Add chicken and bring to a boil; stir in chia seeds and cook until ragout is thickened, about 5 minutes.
